shortcontents.shortcontent:
I) Dawit “Psalter” (fols.3r-224) I-1) Mäzmurä Dawit “Psalms of David” (fols. 3r-165r) I-2) Mäḫalǝyä näbiyat “The Canticles of the Prophets” (fols. 165r-183r) I-3) Mäḫalǝyä mäḫalǝy “Song of Songs” (fols. 183r-193r) I-4) Wǝddase Maryam “The Praise of Mary” (fols. 194ra-213ra) I-5) ʾAnqäṣä bǝrhan “The Gate of Light” (fols. 213ra-220rb) I-6) Mäzmurä dǝngǝl “Psalter of the Virgin” (strophes distributed between sections of Texts I-1, I-2, I-3; fols. 3r-193r) II) Ṣälotä Fäläskinos zä-hagärä Mǝnbužǝr “Prayer of Philoxenus of the Town of Mabbug" (fols. 193v, 220va-224vb)
Additiones 1-3.

donors.donor: The name of Täklä Haymanot is written in a supplication formula added later on fol. 21r. On fol. 44v, a crude note (supplication for the soul), in a secondary hand, mentions a certain Wäldä Krǝstos. A similar note on fol. 54v mentions ʾAkalä Krǝstos; a supplication for the soul of Nǝgǝst ʾAzeb (?) is on fol. 74v. On fol. 193r, there is half-erased note in the same hand, probably mentioning these and other names.

owners.owner: On fol. 222ra, the first part of the original owner's (?) name is retained: Wäldä <...>, the second part has been erased.

txstates.txstate: The Ms. has been resewn. The spine cover has been cut out. The leaves are worn; many are stained with dirt and wax. Some fols. are about to fall apart along the ruling lines. Fol. 64 is damaged by rodents. Fol. 97 is damaged in the bottom right part, part of the text is lost.

bindings.binding: Two wooden boards covered with dark brown tooled leather; textile inlays. Two pairs of sewing stations.

bndecorations.bndecoration: Blind tooled ornament, of poor quality, on the dark brown leather cover (at least 7 tools were used: double line fillet, double circle, small x, x-form, double crescent).

bnothers.bnother: Small holes are visible on the spine fold of the quires, one close to the head and one close to the tail of the codex.

taunit.mr-info: Texts I-1, I-2, I-3: all data are for fol. 4r.

The bottom ruled line or lines were not used by the scribe on fols. 121v-122v.

taunit.mr-info: Texts I-4, I-5: all data are for fol. 195r.

pchangeofhands.pchangeofhand: Numeral ፮ “six” looks like compressed numeral ፯ “seven”. In the beginning, the handwriting is fine, though slightly irregular, with broadly spaced and thin letters. In some parts of the Ms., it becomes irregular and less careful, creating a strong impression that the Ms. was probably written by several hands (though the exact delimitation of text portions is difficult).

rubrications.rubrication:
Nomina sacra (name of St. Mary in Texts I-4, I-5 and I-6 and a few other names); titles and numbers of the Pss. and Canticles; incipits and numbers of Songs; incipit of the strophes of Text I-6; title of Texts I-2, I-3 and I-5; title and incipit of the daily readings of Text I-4; name and traditional interpretation of the Hebrew letters in Ps. 118; refrains of Texts I-4 and I-5 (written out fully or abbreviated); Title o Text II; word mǝʿraf and incipit of chapters in Text II; elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements.
A few lines (alternating with black lines)on the incipit page of Texts I-1, I-4 and II; a few lines (alternating with black lines) of the incipit of Text I-5.

otherdetails.otherdetail: - The traditional titles of the Pss. are missing. - Text II is evidently attributed to Philoxenus of Mabbogh, a 5th-6th cent. Syrian ecclesiastical author.

additional.cont: Fol. 193r: Supplication for the soul of a woman, most probably an owner or donor of the Ms.
Fol. 193r: Ownership note.
additional.det: Name of the owner erased; written in the same hand as Additio 1.

additional.cont: Fol. 220rb: Hymn to the Virgin Mary.
additional.add:
Fol. 220rb: ስብሐት፡ ለኪ፡ ማርያም፡ በኊልቈ፡ አድባር፡ ወአውግር ።
ስብሐት፡ ለኪ፡ ማርያም፡ በኊልቈ፡ ቀላያት፡ ወባሕር ።...
additional.tran:
Fol. 220rb: Praise (be) to you, Mary, as many as mounts and hills.
Praise (be) to you, Mary, as many as valleys and lakes...
additional.det: Written in a later hand, different from that of the main text, in the blank space after Text I-6. The same hymn follows the ʾAnqäṣä bǝrhan in the Psalter EMML no. 2602(6)(b) (but the end of the ʾAnqäṣä bǝrhan in KY-33 is somewhat different from the text printed in GroHymn 383-88). Cp. also EMML nos. 1095-2(11); 2211-2; 3992-13; 3399v-v(1).
